Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{}, then pop it on top of the #pot{} and allow to steam.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{240%g} and @Sliced Mushrooms{120%g}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Stir-fry until golden brown all over, ~{7-8%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Meanwhile, trim the @Pak Choi{1}, then thinly slice widthways.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @Lime{1/2}(cut into wedges).

Once the chicken has browned, add the @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Ginger Puree{15%g}, garlic and pak choi to the pan.

Cook, stirring frequently, until fragrant, ~{2%mins}.

Lower the heat to medium, then add the @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Sambal Paste{15%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Ketjap Manis{25%g} and @Honey{1%tbsp}. Stir to combine.

Stir through the cooked rice and cook until piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add a good squeeze of lime juice from a lime wedge, then remove the pan from the heat. Taste and season with salt, pepper and more lime juice if needed.

Share the chicken fried rice between your #bowls{}.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!